parameters.name: model_id
parameters.label: model_id
parameters.help: Destination id for this model; auto-generated if not specified.

parameters.name: training_frame
parameters.label: training_frame
parameters.help: Id of the training data frame.

parameters.name: validation_frame
parameters.label: validation_frame
parameters.help: Id of the validation data frame.

parameters.name: nfolds
parameters.label: nfolds
parameters.help: Number of folds for K-fold cross-validation (0 to disable or >= 2).

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_models
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_models
parameters.help: Whether to keep the cross-validation models.

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_predictions
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_predictions
parameters.help: Whether to keep the predictions of the cross-validation models.

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_fold_assignment
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_fold_assignment
parameters.help: Whether to keep the cross-validation fold assignment.

parameters.name: fold_assignment
parameters.label: fold_assignment
parameters.help: Cross-validation fold assignment scheme, if fold_column is not specified. The 'Stratified' option will stratify the folds based on the response variable, for classification problems.

parameters.name: fold_column
parameters.label: fold_column
parameters.help: Column with cross-validation fold index assignment per observation.

parameters.name: response_column
parameters.label: response_column
parameters.help: Response variable column.

parameters.name: ignored_columns
parameters.label: ignored_columns
parameters.help: Names of columns to ignore for training.

parameters.name: ignore_const_cols
parameters.label: ignore_const_cols
parameters.help: Ignore constant columns.

parameters.name: score_each_iteration
parameters.label: score_each_iteration
parameters.help: Whether to score during each iteration of model training.

parameters.name: weights_column
parameters.label: weights_column
parameters.help: Column with observation weights. Giving some observation a weight of zero is equivalent to excluding it from the dataset; giving an observation a relative weight of 2 is equivalent to repeating that row twice. Negative weights are not allowed. Note: Weights are per-row observation weights and do not increase the size of the data frame. This is typically the number of times a row is repeated, but non-integer values are supported as well. During training, rows with higher weights matter more, due to the larger loss function pre-factor.

parameters.name: offset_column
parameters.label: offset_column
parameters.help: Offset column. This will be added to the combination of columns before applying the link function.

parameters.name: balance_classes
parameters.label: balance_classes
parameters.help: Balance training data class counts via over/under-sampling (for imbalanced data).

parameters.name: class_sampling_factors
parameters.label: class_sampling_factors
parameters.help: Desired over/under-sampling ratios per class (in lexicographic order). If not specified, sampling factors will be automatically computed to obtain class balance during training. Requires balance_classes.

parameters.name: max_after_balance_size
parameters.label: max_after_balance_size
parameters.help: Maximum relative size of the training data after balancing class counts (can be less than 1.0). Requires balance_classes.

parameters.name: max_confusion_matrix_size
parameters.label: max_confusion_matrix_size
parameters.help: [Deprecated] Maximum size (# classes) for confusion matrices to be printed in the Logs.

parameters.name: checkpoint
parameters.label: checkpoint
parameters.help: Model checkpoint to resume training with.

parameters.name: pretrained_autoencoder
parameters.label: pretrained_autoencoder
parameters.help: Pretrained autoencoder model to initialize this model with.

parameters.name: overwrite_with_best_model
parameters.label: overwrite_with_best_model
parameters.help: If enabled, override the final model with the best model found during training.

parameters.name: use_all_factor_levels
parameters.label: use_all_factor_levels
parameters.help: Use all factor levels of categorical variables. Otherwise, the first factor level is omitted (without loss of accuracy). Useful for variable importances and auto-enabled for autoencoder.

parameters.name: standardize
parameters.label: standardize
parameters.help: If enabled, automatically standardize the data. If disabled, the user must provide properly scaled input data.

parameters.name: activation
parameters.label: activation
parameters.help: Activation function.

parameters.name: hidden
parameters.label: hidden
parameters.help: Hidden layer sizes (e.g. [100, 100]).

parameters.name: epochs
parameters.label: epochs
parameters.help: How many times the dataset should be iterated (streamed), can be fractional.

parameters.name: train_samples_per_iteration
parameters.label: train_samples_per_iteration
parameters.help: Number of training samples (globally) per MapReduce iteration. Special values are 0: one epoch, -1: all available data (e.g., replicated training data), -2: automatic.

parameters.name: target_ratio_comm_to_comp
parameters.label: target_ratio_comm_to_comp
parameters.help: Target ratio of communication overhead to computation. Only for multi-node operation and train_samples_per_iteration = -2 (auto-tuning).

parameters.name: seed
parameters.label: seed
parameters.help: Seed for random numbers (affects sampling) - Note: only reproducible when running single threaded.

parameters.name: adaptive_rate
parameters.label: adaptive_rate
parameters.help: Adaptive learning rate.

parameters.name: rho
parameters.label: rho
parameters.help: Adaptive learning rate time decay factor (similarity to prior updates).

parameters.name: epsilon
parameters.label: epsilon
parameters.help: Adaptive learning rate smoothing factor (to avoid divisions by zero and allow progress).

parameters.name: rate
parameters.label: rate
parameters.help: Learning rate (higher => less stable, lower => slower convergence).

parameters.name: rate_annealing
parameters.label: rate_annealing
parameters.help: Learning rate annealing: rate / (1 + rate_annealing * samples).

parameters.name: rate_decay
parameters.label: rate_decay
parameters.help: Learning rate decay factor between layers (N-th layer: rate * rate_decay ^ (n - 1).

parameters.name: momentum_start
parameters.label: momentum_start
parameters.help: Initial momentum at the beginning of training (try 0.5).

parameters.name: momentum_ramp
parameters.label: momentum_ramp
parameters.help: Number of training samples for which momentum increases.

parameters.name: momentum_stable
parameters.label: momentum_stable
parameters.help: Final momentum after the ramp is over (try 0.99).

parameters.name: nesterov_accelerated_gradient
parameters.label: nesterov_accelerated_gradient
parameters.help: Use Nesterov accelerated gradient (recommended).

parameters.name: input_dropout_ratio
parameters.label: input_dropout_ratio
parameters.help: Input layer dropout ratio (can improve generalization, try 0.1 or 0.2).

parameters.name: hidden_dropout_ratios
parameters.label: hidden_dropout_ratios
parameters.help: Hidden layer dropout ratios (can improve generalization), specify one value per hidden layer, defaults to 0.5.

parameters.name: l1
parameters.label: l1
parameters.help: L1 regularization (can add stability and improve generalization, causes many weights to become 0).

parameters.name: l2
parameters.label: l2
parameters.help: L2 regularization (can add stability and improve generalization, causes many weights to be small.

parameters.name: max_w2
parameters.label: max_w2
parameters.help: Constraint for squared sum of incoming weights per unit (e.g. for Rectifier).

parameters.name: initial_weight_distribution
parameters.label: initial_weight_distribution
parameters.help: Initial weight distribution.

parameters.name: initial_weight_scale
parameters.label: initial_weight_scale
parameters.help: Uniform: -value...value, Normal: stddev.

parameters.name: initial_weights
parameters.label: initial_weights
parameters.help: A list of H2OFrame ids to initialize the weight matrices of this model with.

parameters.name: initial_biases
parameters.label: initial_biases
parameters.help: A list of H2OFrame ids to initialize the bias vectors of this model with.

parameters.name: loss
parameters.label: loss
parameters.help: Loss function.

parameters.name: distribution
parameters.label: distribution
parameters.help: Distribution function

parameters.name: quantile_alpha
parameters.label: quantile_alpha
parameters.help: Desired quantile for Quantile regression, must be between 0 and 1.

parameters.name: tweedie_power
parameters.label: tweedie_power
parameters.help: Tweedie power for Tweedie regression, must be between 1 and 2.

parameters.name: huber_alpha
parameters.label: huber_alpha
parameters.help: Desired quantile for Huber/M-regression (threshold between quadratic and linear loss, must be between 0 and 1).

parameters.name: score_interval
parameters.label: score_interval
parameters.help: Shortest time interval (in seconds) between model scoring.

parameters.name: score_training_samples
parameters.label: score_training_samples
parameters.help: Number of training set samples for scoring (0 for all).

parameters.name: score_validation_samples
parameters.label: score_validation_samples
parameters.help: Number of validation set samples for scoring (0 for all).

parameters.name: score_duty_cycle
parameters.label: score_duty_cycle
parameters.help: Maximum duty cycle fraction for scoring (lower: more training, higher: more scoring).

parameters.name: classification_stop
parameters.label: classification_stop
parameters.help: Stopping criterion for classification error fraction on training data (-1 to disable).

parameters.name: regression_stop
parameters.label: regression_stop
parameters.help: Stopping criterion for regression error (MSE) on training data (-1 to disable).

parameters.name: stopping_rounds
parameters.label: stopping_rounds
parameters.help: Early stopping based on convergence of stopping_metric. Stop if simple moving average of length k of the stopping_metric does not improve for k:=stopping_rounds scoring events (0 to disable)

parameters.name: stopping_metric
parameters.label: stopping_metric
parameters.help: Metric to use for early stopping (AUTO: logloss for classification, deviance for regression and anonomaly_score for Isolation Forest). Note that custom and custom_increasing can only be used in GBM and DRF with the Python client.

parameters.name: stopping_tolerance
parameters.label: stopping_tolerance
parameters.help: Relative tolerance for metric-based stopping criterion (stop if relative improvement is not at least this much)

parameters.name: max_runtime_secs
parameters.label: max_runtime_secs
parameters.help: Maximum allowed runtime in seconds for model training. Use 0 to disable.

parameters.name: score_validation_sampling
parameters.label: score_validation_sampling
parameters.help: Method used to sample validation dataset for scoring.

parameters.name: diagnostics
parameters.label: diagnostics
parameters.help: Enable diagnostics for hidden layers.

parameters.name: fast_mode
parameters.label: fast_mode
parameters.help: Enable fast mode (minor approximation in back-propagation).

parameters.name: force_load_balance
parameters.label: force_load_balance
parameters.help: Force extra load balancing to increase training speed for small datasets (to keep all cores busy).

parameters.name: variable_importances
parameters.label: variable_importances
parameters.help: Compute variable importances for input features (Gedeon method) - can be slow for large networks.

parameters.name: replicate_training_data
parameters.label: replicate_training_data
parameters.help: Replicate the entire training dataset onto every node for faster training on small datasets.

parameters.name: single_node_mode
parameters.label: single_node_mode
parameters.help: Run on a single node for fine-tuning of model parameters.

parameters.name: shuffle_training_data
parameters.label: shuffle_training_data
parameters.help: Enable shuffling of training data (recommended if training data is replicated and train_samples_per_iteration is close to #nodes x #rows, of if using balance_classes).

parameters.name: missing_values_handling
parameters.label: missing_values_handling
parameters.help: Handling of missing values. Either MeanImputation or Skip.

parameters.name: quiet_mode
parameters.label: quiet_mode
parameters.help: Enable quiet mode for less output to standard output.

parameters.name: autoencoder
parameters.label: autoencoder
parameters.help: Auto-Encoder.

parameters.name: sparse
parameters.label: sparse
parameters.help: Sparse data handling (more efficient for data with lots of 0 values).

parameters.name: col_major
parameters.label: col_major
parameters.help: #DEPRECATED Use a column major weight matrix for input layer. Can speed up forward propagation, but might slow down backpropagation.

parameters.name: average_activation
parameters.label: average_activation
parameters.help: Average activation for sparse auto-encoder. #Experimental

parameters.name: sparsity_beta
parameters.label: sparsity_beta
parameters.help: Sparsity regularization. #Experimental

parameters.name: max_categorical_features
parameters.label: max_categorical_features
parameters.help: Max. number of categorical features, enforced via hashing. #Experimental

parameters.name: reproducible
parameters.label: reproducible
parameters.help: Force reproducibility on small data (will be slow - only uses 1 thread).

parameters.name: export_weights_and_biases
parameters.label: export_weights_and_biases
parameters.help: Whether to export Neural Network weights and biases to H2O Frames.

parameters.name: mini_batch_size
parameters.label: mini_batch_size
parameters.help: Mini-batch size (smaller leads to better fit, larger can speed up and generalize better).

parameters.name: categorical_encoding
parameters.label: categorical_encoding
parameters.help: Encoding scheme for categorical features

parameters.name: elastic_averaging
parameters.label: elastic_averaging
parameters.help: Elastic averaging between compute nodes can improve distributed model convergence. #Experimental

parameters.name: elastic_averaging_moving_rate
parameters.label: elastic_averaging_moving_rate
parameters.help: Elastic averaging moving rate (only if elastic averaging is enabled).

parameters.name: elastic_averaging_regularization
parameters.label: elastic_averaging_regularization
parameters.help: Elastic averaging regularization strength (only if elastic averaging is enabled).

parameters.name: export_checkpoints_dir
parameters.label: export_checkpoints_dir
parameters.help: Automatically export generated models to this directory.

parameters.name: auc_type
parameters.label: auc_type
parameters.help: Set default multinomial AUC type.
